Melania and Donald Trump express their condolences to the people of Oman on the passing of Sultan Qaboos bin Sa'id Al Sa'id. They acknowledge his role as the longest-serving leader in the Middle East and his efforts in bringing peace and prosperity to Oman. The statement highlights Sultan Qaboos' commitment to dialogue and achieving peace in the region, emphasizing the importance of listening to all viewpoints. It also recognizes him as a valuable partner and friend to the United States, having worked with nine American presidents. The Trumps pledge to continue strengthening the partnership between the United States and Oman in honor of Sultan Qaboos' memory. They conclude by stating that his powerful legacy will endure.